description: Reticulum v1.1.3 - buffer protocol transfer test vectors

constants.MAX_CHUNK_LEN_note: Maximum input bytes consumed per write() call = 16384
constants.STREAM_DATA_OVERHEAD_note: 2 bytes StreamDataMessage header + 6 bytes Channel envelope
constants.compression_skip_note: Compression loop only runs when chunk_len > 32

small_transfer_vectors.description: Tiny transfer (6 bytes 'Hello\n') — compression skipped (<=32B), single data msg + EOF
Medium transfer (200B random) — single data msg, compression attempted but fails (bz2 overhead > data)
1KB incompressible data — multiple data messages at MAX_DATA_LEN (423B) each + EOF
1KB compressible data (repeated 'A') — 1 compressed data msg + EOF

large_transfer_vectors.description: 50KB incompressible data — raw truncation at MAX_DATA_LEN each
1MB compressible data — compressed messages, summary only
1MB incompressible data — raw messages, summary only

compression_vectors.description: 500B highly compressible — compression succeeds on try 1
500B incompressible — all 3 compression tries fail, raw truncation at MAX_DATA_LEN
16384B (MAX_CHUNK_LEN) partially compressible — shows multi-try compression behavior
Exactly MAX_DATA_LEN (423B) — fits in one raw message, processed_length == input length

eof_vectors.description: Normal EOF after data transfer — write data, then close()
Immediate EOF (no data) — just close() with no prior writes
EOF with non-zero stream_id=42 — verify stream_id encoding preserved

bidirectional_vectors.description: Small bidirectional — A writes 'Hello' (stream_id=0), B writes 'World' (stream_id=1)
Asymmetric bidirectional — A sends 1KB (stream_id=0), B sends 100B (stream_id=1)
Same stream_id=0 both directions — proves stream_id is direction-relative
bidirectional_vectors.note: In create_bidirectional_buffer, receive_stream_id and send_stream_id can both be 0 since direction disambiguates

bidirectional_vectors.description: Non-zero stream_id=5 — verify correct encoding in wire bytes

reassembly_vectors.description: Multi-message reassembly — 1KB incompressible, step-by-step unpack and concatenation
Mixed compression reassembly — some messages compressed, some raw
